{
  "texts": [
    "Among them, node clustering and node sampling are the two main methods.",
    "Node clustering combines similar nodes in the graph into clusters and uses the centers of the clusters as nodes of the coarsened graph.",
    "However, this method involves a node soft assignment matrix, which makes it difficult to fully utilize the sparsity of the graph topology, and thus is computationally inefficient when dealing with large-scale graphs.",
    "Compared to node clustering, node sampling has lower complexity and is more suitable for dealing with large-scale graphs.",
    "It selects nodes with higher scores as nodes for coarsening the graph by evaluating their importance in the graph."
  ]
}